This paper is about testing the performance of a deep reinforcement learning algorithm on deceptive games, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the shortcomings of the algorithm, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper compares the behavior of reinforcement learning-based agents with planning agents based on tree search, which is related to game theory (cs.GT). The games are implemented in a video game framework, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) techniques. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, followed by cs.GT, cs.CV, and cs.RO.
